-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Checking out Parflow from the SVN repository
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

svn co svn+ssh://atlas/usr/gapps/thcs/subversion/pfclm_ms/trunk/pfclm_ms pfclm_ms


Note that this assumes your username is the same on atlas as on the
machine you are checking out.  If not use:

svn co svn+ssh://atlas/usr/gapps/thcs/subversion/pfclm_ms/trunk/pfclm_ms pfclm_ms

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling Parflow on Atlas
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

cd <somewhere>pfclm/ms/src 
./build install

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
Compiling Parflow on CASC Tux Cluster
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------

The system MPI is not compiled for F90 so I different MPI is used.

# Setup the MPI environment
. /usr/casc/samrai/openmpi/openmpi-1.2.6/setup.sh

cd <somewhere>pfclm/ms/src 
./build install





